	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you can get your console to run at 60Hz it should work... does your NES have a switch for that?</div>
<br />The NES PPU has no "50/60 switch". It would have taken an extra pin on the PPU's connector, and pins were (and still are) one of the most expensive things on an IC package.
<br />
<br />If only Nintendo made the PAL NES CPU's clock divider run at 1/15 instead of 1/16, then a lot of the problems wouldn't have been as big.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


